The paper deals with the problem of semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper proposes a novel approach to address the weakly supervised semantic segmentation problem, which involves the use of self-attention mechanism and saliency priors. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques to process textual data, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of multimedia data, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
